sql:
SELECT build_id, stat_name
FROM build_stats
WHERE stat_name = 'success_rate' AND stat_value > 80;

SELECT report_content, creation_date
FROM build_reports
WHERE report_type = 'success';

external_knowledge:
- The "longest average build duration" refers to the project whose builds take the most time on average;
- "Project lead" is the person responsible for managing the project;
- "Build report" contains details about the build process, including success or failure status and any relevant logs.

- Success rate is calculated as the ratio of successful builds to the total number of builds;
- Average build duration is measured in milliseconds;
- Error count includes all errors logged for each build of the project.

